      "writtenOn": "2018-05-15T22:17:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "what if there is \"default\" template defined in a config file. As a user I\u0027d expect that template to be used in this case.\n\nIf you want to add this in a different CL, please leave a TODO\n\ni think this means that we want two magical template names: \"builtin\" and \"default\". builtin is the one above and cannot be overridden by a config. default is used if template is not specified. builtin is used if template execution fails (see below)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 90,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 90,
        "endChar": 22
      },
      "revId": "4f0fc08dce7a2d08013200c48f4fa7dafbf59334",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
