    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3e1cf833_15367a87",
        "filename": "luci_notify/notify/notify.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 90,
      "author": {
        "id": 1273501
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-17T16:10:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This was all handled previously using ListFiles; if you could not retrieve a template, you defaulted to the \"default\" template, or whatever you want to call it in this case.  It would always be set and would always ensure there was a default template to utilize.  If there was a failure retrieving the templates, you have no matching template and get the default.  No additional logic. \n\nBased on the request, the easiest approach is to compare what is requested, what is retrieved, and if a requested template is not retrieved, due to it not existing or error, the contents of that requested template become the default.  This doesnt introduce any complex logic and allows the existing function to operate normally.  Ideally ListFiles would fill this gap and make this a non event.",
      "parentUuid": "81a7387e_a83eec8b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 90,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 90,
        "endChar": 22
      },
      "revId": "4f0fc08dce7a2d08013200c48f4fa7dafbf59334",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a57a559b_2d62f141",
        "filename": "luci_notify/notify/notify.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 90,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-17T16:56:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think I wasn\u0027t clear. Let me make sure I am heard.\n\nThere is a case for having two templates with two different purposes:\n- default template is one that is used if a template was not specified explicitly. It is user-defined.\n- builtin template, or rather \"error\" template, is one that is used if a user-defined template, default or not, failed to execute. It is server-defined, so it is guaranteed to be correct. It may NOT fail. It contains a warning that it had to be used because a user-defined template execution failed, and perhaps it could include the error details.\n\nerror template is essentially a better error handling. We send it out to users because template authors cannot see our server logs.\n\nI\u0027ll add it in a separate CL. My motivation is I don\u0027t want to be bothered by users asking \"what\u0027s wrong with my template? What was the error? Where are the logs?\". The system should provide the answers on its own without developer intervention because developers don\u0027t have time for this.",
      "parentUuid": "3e1cf833_15367a87",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 90,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 90,
        "endChar": 22
      },
