      "message": "we should not fail sending all emails because of one bad template\n\nthis error handling is inconsistent with error handling in buildEmailTemplateMap:\n- L168 only logs an error if a user-defined template is bad\n- this one fails entire function\n\nFWIU in L168, you prefer to use default template if a user-defined template is bad. That SGTM.\n\nDoing so probably means that for each template, we first try to generate an email. If that fails, builtin template is used (which must not fail because it is hardcoded). That means that template\u003c-\u003erecipient matching should happen after we tried to generate emails",
      "revId": "4f0fc08dce7a2d08013200c48f4fa7dafbf59334",
