      "key": {
        "uuid": "18ae1c0a_941c1b83",
        "filename": "luci_notify/notify/notify.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 164,
      "author": {
        "id": 1273501
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-17T16:10:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This ties directly back to not failing when we cannot send an email; why fail on one template and ignore all the others when one fails?\n\nThis goes back to why ListFiles was the chosen path; if you are unable to retrieve a template, for any reason, the user would be sent the default template.  If you fail now, there is no template and the user receives no email at all.  \n\nFailing should be rare, but failing here could prevent all email from being sent rather than a transient error preventing only users of the template not receiving mail.",
      "parentUuid": "b5b0cf0d_3c7ea7c1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 164,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 164,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "4f0fc08dce7a2d08013200c48f4fa7dafbf59334",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dfd9065a_af1be3fc",
        "filename": "luci_notify/notify/notify.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 164,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-17T16:56:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it is a bug to _occasionally_ send an email based on the default template instead of a requested one. Note that this is different from ErrNoConfig. This is a transient failure. Transient failures must be retried. If we return an error here, the whole function will be retried because it is called in a context of a PubSub handler. The handler would return HTTP 500 to the pubsub and pubsub will retry later.",
      "parentUuid": "18ae1c0a_941c1b83",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 164,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 164,
        "endChar": 12
      },
